The paper discusses the self-assembly system of triangular tiles, which is a topic in computational geometry and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the computational power of the triangular tile assembly system, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the assembly of triangles by triangular tiles, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and scientific computing (cs.SC). Finally, the paper provides counter-examples to show that the triangular tile assembly system and the square tile assembly system are not comparable, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
